                <h1>Uranium: The Key to Nuclear Energy</h1>
                <p>Uranium is a dense, radioactive metal critical for nuclear energy production. Found naturally in rocks, it plays a vital role in fueling nuclear reactors and is used in military applications. Despite its energy benefits, uranium mining raises environmental concerns, necessitating safe handling and disposal to prevent contamination.</p>
